hwIPPoolTable.name: hwIPPoolTable
hwIPPoolTable.description: The configuration table of IP address pool.

hwIPPoolEntry.name: hwIPPoolEntry
hwIPPoolEntry.description: The configuration list of IP address pool, which is used to configure the relevant attributes of the IP address pool inside the device.

hwIPPoolName.name: hwIPPoolName
hwIPPoolName.description: IP address pool name, the service module guarantees the exclusiveness of the name.

hwIPPoolRouterIPAddr.name: hwIPPoolRouterIPAddr
hwIPPoolRouterIPAddr.description: Gateway IP address. By default, the mask is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolRouterIPMask.name: hwIPPoolRouterIPMask
hwIPPoolRouterIPMask.description: Gateway mask. By default, the mask is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolPriDNSIPAddr.name: hwIPPoolPriDNSIPAddr
hwIPPoolPriDNSIPAddr.description: Primary DNS IP address. By default, it is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolSecDNSIPAddr.name: hwIPPoolSecDNSIPAddr
hwIPPoolSecDNSIPAddr.description: Second DNS IP address. By default, it is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddr.name: hwIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddr
hwIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddr.description: Primary Netbios IP address. By default, it is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddr.name: hwIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddr
hwIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddr.description: Second Netbios IP address. By default, it is 255.255.255.255.

hwIPPoolIPAddrLease.name: hwIPPoolIPAddrLease
hwIPPoolIPAddrLease.description: IP address lease: 0~(1000*24*60-1)(m) unit: minute. It is allowed not to specify the lease during the adding. The default value is 3*24*60(m).

hwIPPoolStatus.name: hwIPPoolStatus
hwIPPoolStatus.description: Row admin status, either Add or Delete. Supports adding and deletion.

hwIPPoolType.name: hwIPPoolType
hwIPPoolType.description: Value indicates the type of pool, 1-local, 2-relay, 3-server.

hwIPPoolNetwork.name: hwIPPoolNetwork
hwIPPoolNetwork.description: Network ip address of a DHCP Server global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 1

hwIPPoolNetworkMask.name: hwIPPoolNetworkMask
hwIPPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP Server global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP server global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed

hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrString.name: hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrString
hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrString.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip addresses can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip addresses at a time

hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrStringUndo.name: hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrStringUndo
hwIPPoolDNSIPAddrStringUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to be deleted. This object is only for deleting a given ip address of DNS server.

hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrString.name: hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrString
hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrString.description: String of NetBIOS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip addresses can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip addresses at a time

hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrStringUndo.name: hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrStringUndo
hwIPPoolNBNSIPAddrStringUndo.description: A NetBIOS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip address of NetBIOS server

hwIPPoolConflictAutoRecycleInterval.name: hwIPPoolConflictAutoRecycleInterval
hwIPPoolConflictAutoRecycleInterval.description: The flag indicates whether funtion of conflict auto recycle is enabled.

hwIPPoolLowAddr.name: hwIPPoolLowAddr
hwIPPoolLowAddr.description: The lowest IP address in the pool.

hwIPPoolHighAddr.name: hwIPPoolHighAddr
hwIPPoolHighAddr.description: The highest IP address in the pool.

hwIPPoolReqNum.name: hwIPPoolReqNum
hwIPPoolReqNum.description: The number of the request packet.

hwIPPoolReqSucNum.name: hwIPPoolReqSucNum
hwIPPoolReqSucNum.description: The number of the effective request packet.

hwIPSectionTable.name: hwIPSectionTable
hwIPSectionTable.description: The configuration table of IP section.

hwIPSectionEntry.description: IPSection Entry. IP section configuration table, used to manage the IP address of user. There are at most eight address sections to each address pool. Its indexes are hwIPPoolIndex (from the external) and HwIPSectionIndex.

hwIPSectionDesc.name: hwIPSectionDesc
hwIPSectionDesc.description: IP section DESCRIPTION, which can be empty.

hwIPSectionRowStatus.name: hwIPSectionRowStatus
hwIPSectionRowStatus.description: Row admin status, either Add or Delete.

hwIPPoolExtTable.name: hwIPPoolExtTable
hwIPPoolExtTable.description: Extend table of the local address pool. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP servers, you need to configure the lease and option.

hwIPDhcpOptionId1.name: hwIPDhcpOptionId1
hwIPDhcpOptionId1.description: Option ID. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP sever, the option is a configuration parameter, which needs to be defined and explained by the carrier.

hwIPDhcpOptionId2.name: hwIPDhcpOptionId2
hwIPDhcpOptionId2.description: Option ID. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP sever, the option is a configuration parameter, which needs to be defined and explained by the carrier.

hwIPDhcpOptionId3.name: hwIPDhcpOptionId3
hwIPDhcpOptionId3.description: Option ID. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP sever, the option is a configuration parameter, which needs to be defined and explained by the carrier.

hwIPDhcpOptionId4.name: hwIPDhcpOptionId4
hwIPDhcpOptionId4.description: Option ID. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP sever, the option is a configuration parameter, which needs to be defined and explained by the carrier.

hwIPDnsSuffix.name: hwIPDnsSuffix
hwIPDnsSuffix.description: DNS suffix, a string of 0-50 characters. If the value is 0, it indicates that the suffix is deleted.

hwIPDhcpSvrIPRsv.name: hwIPDhcpSvrIPRsv
hwIPDhcpSvrIPRsv.description: mode of IP addresses reserving. 1 indicates leasing management, 2 indicates MAC binding, and other values are invalid.

hwIPPoolIpAddrRenewal.name: hwIPPoolIpAddrRenewal
hwIPPoolIpAddrRenewal.description: ip address renewal: 0~(1000*24*60-1)(m) unit: minute. It is allowed not to specify the renewal during the adding. The default value is 2160(m)

hwIPPoolIpAddrRebinding.name: hwIPPoolIpAddrRebinding
hwIPPoolIpAddrRebinding.description: ip address rebinding: 0~(1000*24*60-1)(m) unit: minute. It is allowed not to specify the renewal during the adding. The default value is 3780(m)

hwIPPoolSIPName1.name: hwIPPoolSIPName1
hwIPPoolSIPName1.description: The name of SIP server. 0 indicates to delete the SIP server.

hwIPPoolSIPName2.name: hwIPPoolSIPName2
hwIPPoolSIPName2.description: The name of SIP server. 0 indicates to delete the SIP server.

hwIPAddressStatusTable.name: hwIPAddressStatusTable
hwIPAddressStatusTable.description: Address status table. It supports the query and setting of status of the local address pool. It does not support the query and setting of status of the remote address pool for the following reasons: 1. The status of the remote address pool cannot be set. 2. The remote and local address pools map different status tables, with different indexes. 3. The remote address pool is managed by the remote equipment, rather than the local equipment. The local equipment displays only the approximate status of the remote address pool.

hwDhcpSvrGroupTable.name: hwDhcpSvrGroupTable
hwDhcpSvrGroupTable.description: Configuration table of the DHCP server group. To monitor the status of the remote DHCP server, you need to configure the local DHCP server. You can configure a maximum of 4094 DHCP server groups. Each server group consists of two DHCP servers. Select the server based on the server status.

hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupIndex.name: hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupIndex
hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupIndex.description: Index of a DHCP server group. When you create an address pool, the equipment adds the hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupIndex entry by default and sends it to the NMS.

hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupName.name: hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupName
hwIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupName.description: Name of the DHCP server group.

hwIPDhcpSvrPriAddr.name: hwIPDhcpSvrPriAddr
hwIPDhcpSvrPriAddr.description: Primary IP address of the DHCP server group.

hwIPDhcpSvrScdiAddr.name: hwIPDhcpSvrScdiAddr
hwIPDhcpSvrScdiAddr.description: Secondary IP address of the DHCP server group.

hwIPDhcpSvrPriState.name: hwIPDhcpSvrPriState
hwIPDhcpSvrPriState.description: Status of the primary DHCP server.

hwIPDhcpScdPriState.name: hwIPDhcpScdPriState
hwIPDhcpScdPriState.description: Status of the secondary DHCP server.

hwIPDhcpSvrAutoRelease.name: hwIPDhcpSvrAutoRelease
hwIPDhcpSvrAutoRelease.description: Whether the server supports the Release packet.

hwIPDhcpSvrRefCount.name: hwIPDhcpSvrRefCount
hwIPDhcpSvrRefCount.description: Number of times the server group is referenced.

hwIPDhcpSvrPriVpnInstance.name: hwIPDhcpSvrPriVpnInstance
hwIPDhcpSvrPriVpnInstance.description: VPN instance of the primary DHCP server.

hwIPDhcpSvrScdVpnInstance.name: hwIPDhcpSvrScdVpnInstance
hwIPDhcpSvrScdVpnInstance.description: VPN instance of the secondary DHCP server.

hwRemotePoolTable.name: hwRemotePoolTable
hwRemotePoolTable.description: Configuration table of the remote address pool. The remote address pool must be configured on the local equipment in the following cases: Users obtain IP addresses through the built-in DHCP client and need to renew the addresses. The equipment needs to record the IP addresses to be renewed. The equipment needs to report the routes of the users.

hwRemoteIPPoolIndex.name: hwRemoteIPPoolIndex
hwRemoteIPPoolIndex.description: Index of an address pool. When you create an address pool, the equipment adds the hwRemoteIPPoolIndex x entry by default and sends it the NMS.

hwRemoteIPPoolName.name: hwRemoteIPPoolName
hwRemoteIPPoolName.description: Name of an address pool. The service module ensures that the name is unique.

hwRemoteIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupID.name: hwRemoteIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupID
hwRemoteIPPoolDhcpSvrGroupID.description: Name of the associated DHCP server group.

hwRemoteIPPoolAvailableStatus.name: hwRemoteIPPoolAvailableStatus
hwRemoteIPPoolAvailableStatus.description: Whether the address pool is locked, 0: locked, 1: not locked.

hwRemoteIPPoolPriDNSIPAddress.name: hwRemoteIPPoolPriDNSIPAddress
hwRemoteIPPoolPriDNSIPAddress.description: IP address of the active DNS server.

hwRemoteIPPoolSecDNSIPAddress.name: hwRemoteIPPoolSecDNSIPAddress
hwRemoteIPPoolSecDNSIPAddress.description: IP address of the standby DNS server.

hwRemoteIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddress.name: hwRemoteIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddress
hwRemoteIPPoolPriNBNSIPAddress.description: IP address of the active NBNS server.

hwRemoteIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddress.name: hwRemoteIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddress
hwRemoteIPPoolSecNBNSIPAddress.description: IP address of the standby NBNS server.

hwRemoteIPPoolLeaseManageEnable.name: hwRemoteIPPoolLeaseManageEnable
hwRemoteIPPoolLeaseManageEnable.description: Whether the address pool lease manage is enable, 0: diable, 1: enable.

hwRemoteIPPoolWeight.name: hwRemoteIPPoolWeight
hwRemoteIPPoolWeight.description: The weight of this Remote IP pool.

hwIPIdleTotalNum.name: hwIPIdleTotalNum
hwIPIdleTotalNum.description: Number of idle addresses on the equipment.

hwIPUsedTotalNum.name: hwIPUsedTotalNum
hwIPUsedTotalNum.description: Number of addresses in use on the equipment.

hwIPConflictTotalNum.name: hwIPConflictTotalNum
hwIPConflictTotalNum.description: Number of conflicting addresses on the equipment.

hwIPExcludeTotalNum.name: hwIPExcludeTotalNum
hwIPExcludeTotalNum.description: Number of excluded addresses on the equipment.

hwIPTotalNum.name: hwIPTotalNum
hwIPTotalNum.description: The total number of IP address.

hwIPUsedPercent.name: hwIPUsedPercent
hwIPUsedPercent.description: The percent of used IP address.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerIP.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerIP
hwIPPoolDhcpServerIP.description: The IP address of DHCP server.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerVRFName.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerVRFName

hwIPPoolDhcpServerSendDisvSpdSec.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerSendDisvSpdSec
hwIPPoolDhcpServerSendDisvSpdSec.description: The interval of discovery packets sent by DHCP server.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadCount.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadCount
hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadCount.description: The threshold of no response packets from DHCP server, when the number count over the threshold, DHCP server is changed from up to down status. The default value is 1.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerNakCount.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerNakCount
hwIPPoolDhcpServerNakCount.description: The threshold of nak packets from DHCP server, when nak packets count over the threshold, DHCP server is changed from up to down status. The default value is 10.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerTimeout.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerTimeout
hwIPPoolDhcpServerTimeout.description: The timeout interval for response packet,the time unit is second and default value is 25 seconds.

hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadTime.name: hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadTime
hwIPPoolDhcpServerDeadTime.description: The interval of DHCP server automatically recover up status, the time unit is minute and default value is 3 minutes.

hwIPPoolOptionTable.name: hwIPPoolOptionTable
hwIPPoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options to DHCP server pools, include option code type and value and so on .

hwIPDhcpOptionId.description: Option ID. When IP addresses are allocated by the built-in DHCP sever, the option is a configuration parameter, which needs to be defined and explained by the carrier.

hwIPDhcpOptionRowStatus.name: hwIPDhcpOptionRowStatus
hwIPDhcpOptionRowStatus.description: This object is used to configuration new rows in this table, modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.Only three actions are used: active(1), createAndGo(4), destroy(6). while configuration new option, you must specify option type and value

hwIPPoolGroupTable.name: hwIPPoolGroupTable
hwIPPoolGroupTable.description: Configuration table of the address Pool Group. IP Pool Group support an aggregation of IP Pools. Many Ip Pools of different gateway can be referenced by IP Pool Group. The max number of IP Pools referenced by an Ip Pool Group is 1024

hwIPPoolGroupEntry.description: The configuration list of IP address pool group, which is used to configure the relevant attributes of the IP address pool group inside the device.

hwIPPoolGroupName.name: hwIPPoolGroupName

hwIPPoolGroupExtIncludePoolName.name: hwIPPoolGroupExtIncludePoolName

hwIPPoolGroupExtRowStatus.name: hwIPPoolGroupExtRowStatus

hwIPPoolGroupIPFreeNum.description: The Free number of IP in IP Pool Group.

hwIPPoolDomainSearchListTable.description: Set the domain search list which is uesed to fill content of DHCP packet option 119. The option is passed from the DHCP Server to the DHCP Client to specify the domain search list used when resolving hostnames using DNS.
